  "title": "The graduation crisis, updated: seed-to-Series-A by cohort",
  "caption": "Seed-to-Series-A conversion rate and time-to-close, by seed cohort year. The 2022 cohort converts at roughly a third of the 2019 rate, over more than 1.5x the time. A thinner seed pipeline (42 seed rounds in 2025 vs. over 100 in 2022) means fewer, more selectively funded companies are still converting at a similar-or-worse rate. Source: Partech 2025 Africa Tech VC Report, via Tech In Africa and The Condia.",
